	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>As for if VP can replace your root spell slot . . . maybe.  But only for traveling purposes.  If you're hunting you better have a root up.  Some things are immune to disease or just highly resistant to it and that can be a pain in the patootie.  <br />
Valorium guardians in HoH are resistant to Disease, and will often resist a VP.  However, I pull the two spawns by slapping one with Malicious Decay, then VP right after that.  VP always sticks after that and sticks for a while.  It's so reliable in doing that, that it's my primary method of pulling in HoH.  The other one has to be dealt with tho, and it's running at you.  I'll train it on the warrior, malo/slow and then go back for the malo/slow on the rooted one.  VP is great if you want reliable root.</p>
	
	
	
