<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Boinshar</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Prophet of War<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Jan 2000<br />
	Location: Springfield Va USA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>VP 2 and 3 adds pushback range, height, and root duration.<br />
<br />
It's highly useful when you pull more than 1 mob--it's a free CC tool that can leave a mob parked out of camp, or push a mob who's already in camp out of it's melee range.<br />
<br />
On raids, when you have melees not watching where they position adds, VP's a great tool that you can use to "help" them.<br />
<br />
VP is an AA skill, so you do not have to wait for the 2.5 sec for spells to come back. Normally, it takes a shaman 3 sec to cast Turgur, wait 2.5 secs, then 2-3 sec to cast root (depending on which root you use). With VP, it takes you 3 sec to cast Turgur, and 2 secs to cast VP--the mob will be taken care of in 5 sec flat, instead of taking up to 7.5-8 secs.<br />
<br />
IMO, it's best use is for helping clerics/enchanters when they need to stand there and channel. Our normal roots would not work--mobs are already in melee range, so we'd normally have to agro, then park. With VP, just face the direction you want the mob to go, and push the button.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Boinshar Harlishambar</div>
	
	
